children.name: Content: Body
children.characters:
It will continue to be updated with improvements and additions from the GOV.UK Design System. With support from the community, I’ll continue to keep this resource updated with new additions and improvements from the GOV.UK Design System and GOV.UK Frontend - and aim to be no more than 3 months behind the latest versions.

When there’s a new update to this resource, I’ll let everyone know on these UK

Government Digital Slack channels:

children.name: Content: Body
children.characters: Did you spot a mistake in the text styles or find a better way to create a component?  Comments, questions and improvements are always welcome. Reach out on any of the slack channels listed above or direct message me at @Joe Horton - DEFRA .

children.name: Content: Body
children.characters:
This Figma file is a community resource of the GOV.UK Design System. The Design System team is not responsible for it and cannot support you with using it.

If you’re new to Figma and/or would like help setting up the styles and components to use in your own projects, you can message me (@Joe Horton - DEFRA) on UK Government Digital Slack or email me (joehortongov@gmail.com) and I’ll respond ASAP. 

Otherwise, you can reach out on the provided slack channels above. 

Enjoy

children.name: Content: Body
children.characters: In order to use the styles and components, you’ll need to make sure you have GDS Transport font downloaded on your computer. If you’re not sure whether you should be using GDS Transport, read the Service Manual guide on making your service look like GOV.UK.

children.name: Content: Body
children.characters:
The next step is to use the published components and styles in a new figma file.  
In your working file, you’ll be able to add the styles and components from this file using the Assets navigation tab next to the Layers navigation tab.
